George Elsby (6 June 1902 – 20 June 1953) was an English cricketer.  Elsby was a right-handed batsman who bowled right-arm medium pace.  He was born in Tunstall, Staffordshire.
Elsby made a single first-class match for Wales against the Marylebone Cricket Club in 1927.  In this match, he scored 14 runs in Wales first-innings, before being dismissed by Alec Kennedy, while in their second-innings he was dismissed by the same bowling for 22 runs.  During the course of the match he bowled 11 wicket-less overs.He died in Ipswich, Suffolk on 20 June 1953.
